KANSAS NEWS
K-State students earn fall 2024 semester honors
Over 4,600 Kansas State University students achieved semester honors for exceptional academic performance in Fall 2024, maintaining a GPA of 3.75 or higher across at least 12 graded credits. This accomplishment merits dean commendations and is documented in their academic records, highlighting the students' dedication and success in their studies.
KNDY LOCAL NEWS
Nemaha County Administrator Resigns, Successor Named
Nemaha County Administrator Robert Reece resigned effective October 1, with the County Commission accepting his resignation on August 25 without providing a reason. Reece, who began his role in March, will remain as a budgetary advisor. Austin Parker is appointed as the transitional administrator, receiving an additional $65,000 salary.
